| A-101 | The implemented M05 terminal path does not yet own numeric interest rate, repayment date, penal rate, charges policy, or a distinct dispute-resolution clause; therefore a source-complete 13-field Term Sheet must remain configuration-blocked when an approved template declares those missing fields. A test that directly inserts a fully populated `SanctionDecision` proves renderer capability only, not an end-to-end M05-to-M06 workflow. | A-079 deliberately retained honest null/empty sanction terms because no approved frozen source supplies them. 008B correctly refuses missing required merge facts, but its positive tracer bypasses the real terminal writer and cannot establish M06-FR-013 production readiness. Inventing rates, dates, fees, or legal clauses would violate DECISION_POLICY §1.3. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` §15.1 and M06-FR-013; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §§25.8/26.4; Epic 008 digest V10 p.17 §4.9; A-079; architecture review `2026-07-14_093142_architecture_review` | 008B3 and a future source-governed sanction-term/configuration owner | High | Yes | 2026-07-14 | 008B3 must label the real-path blocker and renderer fixture honestly. When governance identifies the authoritative rate/repayment/fee/clause owners and approval semantics, freeze those facts before terminal decision and add a real public-workflow tracer; never derive them from current mutable policy or test-only rows. |
